comments:
Abolished 31.3.1904 and added to the parish of Burton upon 
    Trent.

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the East Staffordshire unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (h).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Hanbury. See also Table 2, note (f).

On 20.10.1844 a detached part of the parish of Foston & 
    Scropton was transferred from Derbyshire to Staffordshire; this area became part of the parish of Yoxall 
    on 29.9.1890, so that thereafter Foston & Scropton 
    was entirely in Derbyshire. See also Table 2, notes (c) and (g).
Abolished 25.3.1885 and added to the parish of Hilton.

Abolished 31.3.1904 and added to the parish of Burton upon 
    Trent.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Hanbury. See also Table 2, note (f).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Hanbury. See also Table 2, note (f).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Horninglow. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Stapenhill in the borough of 
    Burton upon Trent became part of Staffordshire and in 1894 the remaining Derbyshire 
    parts of the parish became parts of the parishes of Bretby and Drakelow, so 
    that thereafter Stapenhill was wholly in Staffordshire. Abolished 31.3.1904 
    and added to the parish of Burton upon Trent.

In 1889 the part of the parish of Winshill in the borough of Burton 
    upon Trent became part of Staffordshire, in 1894 the remaining part in Derbyshire 
    became part of the parish of Newton Solney, so that thereafter Winshill was 
    wholly in Staffordshire. Abolished 31.3.1904 and added to the parish of 
    Burton upon Trent.

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of Tutbury. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).
